<div id="Idea_2806"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2806-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2806">Make US Census procedures transparent&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4024-4049">michael</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The US census determines the apportionment of voting districts. This process is being overseen by the executive branch, which has a partisan interest in the outcome. We should do everything to insure the US census process is not politicized.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2806" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2806', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=2806')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2806"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=census">census</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2806"></div>
