<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2765"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2765-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2765">Webcast all legal trials and government meetings&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">pulierml</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">As much as possible open all government meetings to the public and all "public" legal trials by streaming them on the Web. Participants will know they are being watched and judges won't fall asleep or become rude. Citizen watchdogs will have ready access. Advocacy groups could archive and replay material of interest. The "public record" will not just be text in a storeroom but will also be available as on-demand video.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2765" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2765', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=2765')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2765"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=streaming video internet on-demand watchdog sunshine">streaming video internet on-demand watchdog sunshine</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2765"></div>
</div></td>
